comments.content: Deletion or duplication of the region chr7:75,138,294-76,064,412, also known as 7q11.23 distal (OMIM # 613729), are rare genetic disorders and can cause different neurological and neuropsychiatric symptoms. Patients are often observed with epilepsy and neurodevelopmental delay.
